<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1085,697,953]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">
This species has been described by 
<bibRefCitation author="AUBE C" box="[551,739,697,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" refId="ref4478" refString="AUBE C. (1838): Hydrocanthares et gyriniens. - In: DEJEAN P. F., Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Vol. 6. - Paris: Mequignon Pere et Fils, xvi + 804 pp." type="book" year="1838">AUBÉ (1838: 554)</bibRefCitation>
from &quot; 
<collectingCountry box="[813,889,697,719]" name="Egypt" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Égypte</collectingCountry>
&quot; (African part and 
<collectingRegion box="[178,234,726,748]" country="Egypt" name="Shamal Sina'" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Sinai</collectingRegion>
). So far it was, additionally, known from 
<collectingCountry box="[702,776,726,748]" name="Kuwait" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[837,976,726,748]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="NILSSON A" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" refId="ref5260" refString="NILSSON A. N. (2012): Catalogue of Palearctic Dytiscidae (Coleoptera). Internet version 2012 - 01 - 01. - Available from http: // www 2. emg. umu. se / projects / biginst / andersn / Cat main. htm (accessed in August 2012)." type="url" year="2012">NILSSON 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="SHARP D" box="[252,447,755,777]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" pagination="179 - 1003" refId="ref5543" refString="SHARP D. (1882) On aquatic carnivorous Coleoptera or Dytiscidae. - Scientific Transactions of the Royal Dublin Society (2) 2: 179 - 1003 + pls. 7 - 18." type="journal article" year="1882">SHARP (1882: 391)</bibRefCitation>
gave also the areas &quot; 
<collectingCountry box="[668,734,755,777]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Persia</collectingCountry>
&quot; and &quot;northern 
<collectingCountry box="[899,953,755,777]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">India</collectingCountry>
&quot; which later on, however, have not been accepted by any author and are most probably due to a misidentification of another species. We can report the following record from close to the Iraqi border: 4, 4, &quot; 
<date box="[466,569,843,865]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" value="2010-12-09">12.9.2010</date>
<collectingCountry box="[578,621,844,865]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[635,744,843,865]" country="Iran" name="Khuzestan" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Khuzestan</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity box="[757,811,843,865]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" unit="km" value="8.0">8 km</quantity>
SE Abadan, altitude 
<quantity box="[1038,1081,843,865]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" unit="m" value="8.0">8 m</quantity>
, Darvishzadeh leg., ca. 
<geoCoordinate box="[424,498,872,894]" degrees="30.29" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" precision="555" value="30.29">30.29N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[510,585,872,894]" degrees="48.36" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" precision="555" value="48.36">48.36E</geoCoordinate>
, pond&quot; (CHF) (
<figureCitation box="[757,838,872,894]" captionStart="Fig 23" captionStartId="2.[178,212,219,241]" captionText="Fig 23). The label data are: &quot;21.7.2011 Iran, Hormozgan prov., NE Bandar Abbas, ca. 5 km ENE Rudan (Roodān), Rudan stream, 27.4771N 57.2578E, alt. 210 m, pump in gravels, Pešić leg. (IR22)&quot;, &quot;Glareadessus franzi Wewalka &amp; Biström, Fery det. 2011&quot; (CHF). This collecting site is illustrated in Fig. 21; it is situated only about 25 km west of the type locality. A comparison with a photo of the locus typicus in WEWALKA &amp; BISTRÖM (1998: 63; fig. 12) shows that both localities appear rather similar. Another female has been found (also by means of a pump) ca. 60 km WNW of Rudan (triangle (1) in Fig. 23; the collecting site is illustrated in Figs 19 and 20); the label data are: &quot;18.7.2011 Iran, Hormozgan prov., N Bandar Abass, Banglayan village, stream, 27.7616N 56.5400E, alt. 577 m, pump in gravels, Pešić leg. (IR19)&quot;, the DNA extraction voucher number &quot;IBE-RA 640&quot; and &quot;parts of abdomen lost due to sequencing&quot; and the same determination label as above (CHF)." pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
; square 1). This is the f i r s t r e c o r d of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="AUBE" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[423,520,902,924]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hyphoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solieri">
<emphasis box="[423,520,902,924]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">H. solieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[583,627,902,923]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Iran</collectingCountry>
. To our knowledge a photo of the habitus of this species has never been provided before (
<figureCitation box="[632,708,931,953]" captionStart="Figs 13-15" captionStartId="11.[178,218,716,736]" captionTargetBox="[190,1074,237,674]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[178,1084,219,696]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 13-15: Habitus of (13) Hyphoporus solieri, (14) Hygrotus orthogrammus, (15) Canthydrus laetabilis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367840/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
