<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1085,968,1049]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[178,238,968,990]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Notes</emphasis>
: We could not recognise extern morphological differences to specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[178,242,998,1019]" name="Egypt" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Egypt</collectingCountry>
; the male genitalia also equal those of Egyptian specimens. It seems to be likely that the species occur also in the southern parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[689,733,1028,1049]" name="Iraq" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Iraq</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
